an novels]]\n", "name_user": "Wbm1058", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix miscapitalization (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grahana_(novel)"}
{"title_page": "Chily", "text_new": "{{MOS|date=April 2020}}\n{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = solo_singer\n| name             = Chily\n| image            = Chily, rappeur fran\u00e7ais.jpg\n| alias            =\n| birth_name       = Charry Masengo\n| birth_place      = [[Chevilly-Larue]], France\n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1999}}\n| years_active     = 2017\u2014present\n| genre            = [[Trap music|Trap]], [[hip-hop]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Koba LaD]] \u00b7 [[Naza (rapper)|Naza]] \u00b7 [[Hamza (rapper)|Hamza]]\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], [[MC|animator]]\n| label            = [[Sony Music Entertainment]] \u00b7 Himalaya \u00b7 Bikini Botoom Music \u00b7 C'Est Rien C'Est La Rue\n}}\n\n'''Charry Masengo''' (born 1999), best known as '''Chily''', is a French rapper of [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] origin. In 2018, he was recognised after the release of the single \"Pernambucano\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.raprnb.com/artiste/chily/|title=Chily : actu, albums et paroles|website=RAPRNB|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> then, in 2020, he released his first album named \"5\u00e8me Chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique)\".<ref>{{Citation|title=\u200e5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique) by Chily|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/5%C3%A8me-chambre-tr%C3%A8s-mystique/1495632777|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> In August 2019, he was under arrest after fighting two police officers, sentenced with two years imprisonment, he later escaped from the prison.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/val-de-marne-94/chevilly-chily-figure-montante-du-rap-echappe-a-la-prison-apres-des-violences-05-08-2019-8129223.php|title=Chevilly : Chily, figure montante du rap, \u00e9chappe \u00e0 la prison apr\u00e8s des violences|last=\u00e0 20h10|first=Par Denis Courtine avec Bartolom\u00e9 SimonLe 5 ao\u00fbt 2019|last2=\u00c0 20h16|first2=Modifi\u00e9 Le 5 Ao\u00fbt 2019|date=2019-08-05|website=leparisien.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life ===\nBorn in 1999, Chily was heavily interested in music from a young age, specifically [[Ndombolo|N'dombolo music]]. Congolese artists like [[Werrason]], [[Koffi Olomide]], [[Ferre Gola]] or [[King Kester Emeneya]], were artists he listened to most. He started his musical journey in late 2000s with his cousins after being a founding member of the group 5\u00e8me Chambre<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j39zfr3tf_o Chily : \"Le succ\u00e8s de quelqu'un, c'est des portes ouvertes aux autres\" | Interview] | [[YouTube]]</ref>. He is inspired by Congolese animator B\u00e9b\u00e9 K\u00e9rozene<ref> [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DVec8-sCZjo CHILY : San Pellegrino, l\u2019influence de ses origines congolaises sur sa musique... | SKIP SKIP] | [[YouTube]]</ref>.\n\n=== Actual life ===\n\n==== Musical career ====\nMid 2010s, Chily started uploading [[freestyle rap|freestyles]] to [[YouTube]] and [[Dailymotion]]. His series <nowiki>''</nowiki>''Compl\u00e8tement R\u00e9banav''<nowiki>''</nowiki><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://generations.fr/video/clip/48323/chily-devoile-un-nouvel-episode-de-sa-serie-de-freestyles-completement-rebanav|title=Generations|last=Generations|date=2019-05-31|website=Generations|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>, became popular around [[Europe]] and [[France]]. Then, in 2018, he released his first hit <nowiki>''</nowiki>''Pernambucano''<nowiki>'', included in his first album ''</nowiki>''En attendant...''<nowiki>''. Summer of 2019, was when Chily was internationally famous after the release of the singles ''</nowiki>''Bina''<nowiki>'' and ''</nowiki>''San Pellegrino''<nowiki>''</nowiki>. His first concert will be in the [[Casino de Paris]] in 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoconcert.com/artiste/chily-182754/concerts.html|title=CHILY en concert : place de concert, billet, ticket et liste des concerts|website=www.infoconcert.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>, after the release of his second album <nowiki>''</nowiki>''5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique)''<nowiki>''</nowiki>. He claims that his music is not simply trap, but is ''Bikini bottom music''.\n\n== Legal issues ==\nIn August 2019, Chily was arrested after assaulting two police officers with a friend. He was sentenced to two years in prison, but he later escaped<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Portal|Biography|Democratic Republic of the Congo|Music\n}}\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n\n* En attendant... (2019)\n* 5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique) (2020)\n\n== References list ==\n<references />\n[[Category:French rappers]]\n", "text_old": "{{MOS|date=April 2020}}\n{{Copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = solo_singer\n| name             = Chily\n| image            = Chily, rappeur fran\u00e7ais.jpg\n| alias            =\n| birth_name       = Charry Masengo\n| birth_place      = [[Chevilly-Larue]], France\n| birth_date       = {{birth year and age|1999}}\n| years_active     = 2017\u2014present\n| genre            = [[Trap music|Trap]], [[hip-hop]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Koba LaD]] \u00b7 [[Naza (rapper)|Naza]] \u00b7 [[Hamza (rapper)|Hamza]]\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], [[MC|animator]]\n| label            = [[Sony Music Entertainment]] \u00b7 Himalaya \u00b7 Bikini Botoom Music \u00b7 C'Est Rien C'Est La Rue\n}}\n\n'''Charry Masengo''' (born 1999), best known as '''Chily''', is a French rapper of [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] origin. In 2018, he got recognised after the release of the single \"Pernambucano\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.raprnb.com/artiste/chily/|title=Chily : actu, albums et paroles|website=RAPRNB|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> then, in 2020, he released his first album named \"5\u00e8me Chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique)\".<ref>{{Citation|title=\u200e5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique) by Chily|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/5%C3%A8me-chambre-tr%C3%A8s-mystique/1495632777|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> In August 2019, he was under arrest after fighting two police officers, with a sentence of two years and later, he escaped from the prison.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/val-de-marne-94/chevilly-chily-figure-montante-du-rap-echappe-a-la-prison-apres-des-violences-05-08-2019-8129223.php|title=Chevilly : Chily, figure montante du rap, \u00e9chappe \u00e0 la prison apr\u00e8s des violences|last=\u00e0 20h10|first=Par Denis Courtine avec Bartolom\u00e9 SimonLe 5 ao\u00fbt 2019|last2=\u00c0 20h16|first2=Modifi\u00e9 Le 5 Ao\u00fbt 2019|date=2019-08-05|website=leparisien.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life ===\nBorn in 1999, at his short age, Chily was heavily interested in music, specifically [[Ndombolo|N'dombolo music]]. Congolese artists like [[Werrason]], [[Koffi Olomide]], [[Ferre Gola]] or [[King Kester Emeneya]], were the ones that he listened to more. He started music in late 2000s with his cousins after being a founding member of the group 5\u00e8me Chambre<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j39zfr3tf_o Chily : \"Le succ\u00e8s de quelqu'un, c'est des portes ouvertes aux autres\" | Interview] | [[YouTube]]</ref>. He is inspired by Congolese animator B\u00e9b\u00e9 K\u00e9rozene<ref> [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DVec8-sCZjo CHILY : San Pellegrino, l\u2019influence de ses origines congolaises sur sa musique... | SKIP SKIP] | [[YouTube]]</ref>.\n\n=== Actual life ===\n\n==== Musical career ====\nMid 2010s, Chily started uploading [[freestyle rap|freestyles]] to [[YouTube]] and [[Dailymotion]]. His series <nowiki>''</nowiki>''Compl\u00e8tement R\u00e9banav''<nowiki>''</nowiki><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://generations.fr/video/clip/48323/chily-devoile-un-nouvel-episode-de-sa-serie-de-freestyles-completement-rebanav|title=Generations|last=Generations|date=2019-05-31|website=Generations|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>, became popular around [[Europe]] and [[France]]. Then, in 2018, he released his first hit <nowiki>''</nowiki>''Pernambucano''<nowiki>'', included in his first album ''</nowiki>''En attendant...''<nowiki>''. Summer of 2019, was when Chily got internationally famous after the release of the singles ''</nowiki>''Bina''<nowiki>'' and ''</nowiki>''San Pellegrino''<nowiki>''</nowiki>. His first concert will be in the [[Casino de Paris]] in 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoconcert.com/artiste/chily-182754/concerts.html|title=CHILY en concert : place de concert, billet, ticket et liste des concerts|website=www.infoconcert.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>, after the release of his second album <nowiki>''</nowiki>''5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique)''<nowiki>''</nowiki>. He claims that his music is not simply trap, but is ''Bikini botoom music''.\n\n== Legal issues ==\nIn August 2019, Chily was arrested after assaulting two police officers with a friend. He was sentenced to two years in prison, but he later escaped<ref name=\":0\" />.\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Portal|Biography|Democratic Republic of the Congo|Music\n}}\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n\n* En attendant... (2019)\n* 5\u00e8me chambre (Tr\u00e8s mystique) (2020)\n\n== References list ==\n<references />\n[[Category:French rappers]]\n", "name_user": "Itsthatgirlb", "label": "safe", "comment": "copy edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chily"}
