oronavirus death toll crosses 150,000: Live updates|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-deaths-35000-live-updates-200416234342434.html |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=17 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417235405/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-deaths-35000-live-updates-200416234342434.html|archive-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> Wuhan has also revised its official death toll from the coronavirus by 50% from 1,290 to 3,869; with local authorities citing incorrect reporting, delays, and omissions. This brings the country's death toll to at least 4,642.<ref>{{cite news |title=China's Wuhan raises Covid-19 death toll by 50%, citing early lapses |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/04/17/china039s-wuhan-raises-covid-19-death-toll-by-50-citing-early-lapses#cxrecs_s |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |agency=[[Reuters]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417102214/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/04/17/china039s-wuhan-raises-covid-19-death-toll-by-50-citing-early-lapses |archivedate=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: China outbreak city Wuhan raises death toll by 50% |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-52321529 |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=[[BBC News]] |date=17 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200417212529/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-52321529 |archivedate=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Qin |first1=Amy |title=China Raises Coronavirus Death Toll by 50% in Wuhan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/world/asia/china-wuhan-coronavirus-death-toll.html |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=[[New York Times]] |date=17 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200417163133/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/world/asia/china-wuhan-coronavirus-death-toll.html |archivedate=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Al Jazeera 17 April reports\" /> \n*France reports 761 new deaths, bringing the total to 18,681. The French government also confirms that 1,081 crew members of the French aircraft carrier [[French aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle|''Charles De Gaulle'']] have tested positive for the coronavirus. 524 sailors have also shown symptoms while 24 remain in hospitals.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 17 April reports\" /> \n*Italy has reported 575 deaths, bringing the death toll to 22,745. The country has reported 3,493 new cases, bringing the total to 172,434.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 17 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 69 new cases, bringing the total to 5,251. 2,967 patients have recovered while 2,198 cases are receiving treatment at the country's health facilities. Malaysia also reports two new deaths, bringing the death toll to 86.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos Jr |first1=Joseph |title=Covid-19: 69 new cases, death toll now at 86 |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/17/covid-19-69-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-86 |accessdate=17 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=17 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417100134/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/17/covid-19-69-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-86 |archivedate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The Netherlands reports 1,235 new cases, bringing the total to 30,449. The country has reported 144 deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,459.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 17 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand has reported eight new cases (two confirmed and six probable), bringing the total to 1,409 (1,080 confirmed and 307 probable). NZ health authorities have reported 46 recoveries, bringing the total to 816. In addition, New Zealand authorities confirm two deaths, bringing the total to 11.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=17 April 2020|archive-url=|archive-