akaanda (novel)|Uttarakaanda]]\n{{div col end}} \n=== S.L. Bhyrappa's autobiography ===\n\n*[[Bhitti]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:20th-century Indian novels]]\n[[Category:Kannada novels]]\n[[Category:1952 novels]]\n[[Category:1952 Indian novels]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox book\n| name          = Bheemakaaya\n| title_orig    = \n| translator    = \n| image         = SL-Bhyrappa-Bheemakaaya.jpg\n| caption       = Cover of the novel\n| image_size    = 250px\n| author        = [[S L Bhyrappa]]\n| illustrator   = \n| cover_artist  = \n| country       = [[India]]\n| language      = [[Kannada]]\n| series        = \n| subject       = [[Psychology]], [[Philosophy]]\n| genre         = [[Philosophical fiction]]\n| published     = 1958 Sahitya Bhandara, Bangalore\n| media_type    = Print ([[Hardcover]])\n| pages         = \n| isbn          = \n| oclc          = \n| preceded_by   = Gatha Janma Matteradu Kathegalu\n| followed_by   = Belaku Mooditu\n| website       = [http://slbhyrappa.in/bheemakaya/ ''Official website'']\n}}\n\n'''''Bheemakaaya''''' is the first novel written by [[S.L. Bhyrappa]], it got published on 1952. Bheemakaaya means giant, massive, and this book is about a wrestler and his life. Bhyrappa was 18 years old when he was written this article.{{clarify|date=May 2016}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://booksrevisit.blogspot.in/2014/12/BhittiSLBhyrappaAutobiographyBookReview.html|title=Bheemakaaya Review }} {{unreliable?|date=January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15818019-bhimakaya|title=Bheemakaaya reviews}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n=== S.L. Bhyrappa's novels ===\n\n{{div col|colwidth=18em}}\n*[[Dharmashree]]\n*[[Doora saridaru]]\n*[[Matadana]]\n*[[Naayi Neralu (Novel)|Naayi Neralu]]\n*[[Tabbaliyu Neenade Magane (novel)|Tabbaliyu Neenade Magane]]\n*[[Gruhabhanga]]\n*[[Nirakarana]]\n*[[Grahana (novel)|Grahana]]\n*[[Daatu]]\n*[[A